eld direction. We find that\n${\\sigma_{ac}}$ increases abruptly when the B field is tilted from the $a$ axis\nwithin the $ab$ plane. Our WFTB model also shows significant anomalous Hall\nconductivity induced by avoided level crossings even in the absence of Weyl\nnodes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 9 Oct 2019 20:37:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-29"}
