ation heat. The first-order\ntransition without latent heat at TK2 = 122.4 K induces ordered Phase 3,\nbecomes underlying below Tg in further heating and induces an enthalpy excess\nat Tm which is used to predict TK2. This description agrees with the broken\nbond and solid fractal structure percolation theories.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 Oct 2019 07:15:43 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 14 Oct 2019 07:17:39 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 11 Nov 2019 07:48:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-02-19"}
