ns in the dust composition could also\npartly contribute to the low beta we observe. The steepness of the beta radial\ngradient depends strongly on the envelope mass, which might favor a scenario\nwhere large grains are built in high density protostellar disks and transported\nto the intermediate envelope radii, for example with the help of outflows and\nwinds.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 Oct 2019 15:34:56 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 12 Nov 2019 12:39:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-27"}
